comment: If two words ` A , B ` are related under the free group equivalence, then there exist two extension sequences ` a , b ` such that ` a ` ends at ` A ` , ` b ` ends at ` B ` , and ` a ` and ` B ` have the same starting point. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 1-Oct-2015.)
